{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb4419c4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s466"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"466"},"text":"§ 466.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reserves of banks in dependencies or insular possessions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"National banks, or banks organized under local laws, located in a dependency or insular possession or any part of the United States outside the continental United States, may remain nonmember banks, and shall in that event maintain reserves and comply with all the conditions now provided by law regulating them; or said banks may with the consent of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, become member banks of any one of the reserve districts, and shall in that event take stock, maintain reserves, and be subject to all the other provisions of this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb4419c5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s19/h"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 19(h)","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 19 (par. 11), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/270"},"text":"38 Stat. 270","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1914-08-15/ch252"},"text":"Aug. 15, 1914, ch. 252","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/692"},"text":"38 Stat. 692","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1917-06-21/ch32/s10"},"text":"June 21, 1917, ch. 32, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/240"},"text":"40 Stat. 240","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-23/ch614"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935, ch. 614","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 203(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/704"},"text":"49 Stat. 704","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/70/s8/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–70, § 8(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/142"},"text":"73 Stat. 142","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 19(h), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597/s2/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–597, § 2(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-21"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/824"},"text":"80 Stat. 824","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb4419c6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb4419c7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddb4419c8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6"},"text":"act Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/251"},"text":"38 Stat. 251","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Reserve Act. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see References in Text note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s226"},"text":"section 226 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb4419c9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of subsec. (h), formerly eleventh par., of section 19 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913","children":[],"tail":", as redesignated by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–597","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb4419ca-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1959—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/70"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–70","children":[],"tail":" struck out “in Alaska or” before “in a dependency”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddb4419cb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"iddb4419cc-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 203(a) of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935","children":[],"tail":", changed name of Federal Reserve Board to Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
